Infinix Zero 5 Pro - Get Smarter By Doubling The Storage!   
Infinix introduced another variant of Zero 5 to provide extra space to Pro users who want extra storage to keep all data in one place. They gonna get this storage by paying some extra money as compare to the basic variant. Infinix Zero 5 Pro is painted with separate range of colors to make it look different from the 64 GB variant of this smartphone. There are three color option which you gonna get in your new Infinix's Zero 5 Pro and it includes Black, Bronze and Gold colors and its up to you that which color is your favorite one that you gonna buy for yourself. If we talk about the Infinix Zero 5's design then you will see a unibody design carved from single metal that looks shiny and cozy form all of its angles. On the front side you will get the 5.98 inches display. Zero 5 Pro by Infinix got the same display made by JDI and technology used is LTPS IPS matrix that supports FHD display with a resolution of 1080 x 1920 pixels where the pixel density of Infinix 5 Pro is 368 pixels per inch. 2.5D curved edge glass is planted which is protected with special corning gorilla glass. Engine compartment is consist to 2.6 GHz octa core processor that makes 5 Pro powerful enough to take care of the running processes inside. MediaTek MT6757 Helio P25 chipset is carrying the weight of all the hardware while GPU of Infinix Zero's 5 Pro is also planted on the same chip that take care of all graphic performance of the device. 6 GB of RAM is hired to tackle multi-tasking of Zero 5 Pro while Nougat operating system keeps everything in order. 
